From 387dd94ae3c307024b85013bb42f118337c00b67 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Josua Mayer <josua@solid-run.com>
Date: Fri, 6 Mar 2026 14:51:34 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] mmc: fsl_esdhc: call cyclic schedule() during dma transfers

Large-size transfers from especially microsd cards can take a long time
and easily exceed a typical 30s watchdog timer, leading to unexpected
reset e.g. during load commands.

Add call to the cyclic framework schedule() function to
esdhc_send_cmd_common to ensure that background tasks such as watchdog
servicing still take place.

This fixes in particular an issue on LX2160 when loading a large disk
image from microSD and writing to eMMC would be interrupted because
expired watchdog reset the system after 30 seconds.

Signed-off-by: Josua Mayer <josua@solid-run.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/fsl_esdhc.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/fsl_esdhc.c b/drivers/mmc/fsl_esdhc.c
index 05a6d0ce156..3e16c099732 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/fsl_esdhc.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/fsl_esdhc.c
@@ -459,6 +459,9 @@ static int esdhc_send_cmd_common(struct fsl_esdhc_priv *priv, struct mmc *mmc,
 					err = -ECOMM;
 					goto out;
 				}
+
+				/* yield to cyclic framework background tasks */
+				schedule();
 			} while ((irqstat & flags) != flags);
 
 			/*
-- 
2.51.0

